{"type":"message","id":"2143981b","parentId":"db83dbed","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:18.150Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_yjZjS3WmwtVcbJrlnwDjcE9g","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Audit Report Template\n\n## Summary\nBrief overview of the audit scope, entry points examined, and overall health of the codebase.\n\n## Architecture Observations\n- **UI Layer**: Entry points identified (Visualforce, LWC, Flows).\n- **Controller Layer**: How business logic is organized.\n- **Service Layer**: Reusable services and utilities.\n- **Integration Layer**: External callouts and APIs.\n- **Data Model**: Objects and fields involved.\n- **Automation**: Triggers, flows, process builders.\n\n## Technical Risks\n- **Governor Limits**: SOQL in loops, DML in loops, heap size.\n- **Performance**: Selective queries, indexing, view state.\n- **Maintainability**: Code duplication, tight coupling, lack of separation of concerns.\n- **Testing**: Coverage gaps, missing negative tests.\n\n## Security Risks\n- **FLS/CRUD**: Missing security checks.\n- **Injection**: SOQL injection, XSS.\n- **Authentication**: Insecure callouts, exposed secrets.\n- **Sharing**: Over‑exposed data.\n\n## Performance Risks\n- **Query selectivity**: Non‑indexed fields in WHERE clauses.\n- **Bulkification**: Triggers not handling bulk data.\n- **View state**: Large Visualforce view state.\n- **Async**: Long‑running operations not offloaded.\n\n## Refactor Opportunities\n- **Extract methods**: Long methods that can be split.\n- **Introduce services**: Move logic out of controllers.\n- **Use standard features**: Replace custom code with Salesforce‑provided functionality.\n- **Improve naming**: Unclear variable/method names.\n- **Add logging**: Missing error logging.\n\n## Design Alignment\nCompare the actual code behavior with the architectural design (if a `salesforce‑architect` output is available).\n\n- **Matches design**: Code implements the intended architecture.\n- **Deviations**: Where code diverges from design, with impact.\n- **Missing components**: Designed elements not found in code.\n- **Unexpected additions**: Code elements not in the design.\n\n## Recommendations\nPrioritized list of actions:\n1. **Critical**: Security flaws, governor‑limit risks.\n2. **High**: Performance issues, maintainability problems.\n3. **Medium**: Code style improvements, logging additions.\n4. **Low**: Naming, comments.\n\n## Appendix\n- **Files examined**: List of files loaded during the audit.\n- **Snippets extracted**: Methods and blocks reviewed.\n- **Dependency graph**: High‑level view of class dependencies.\n- **Execution trace**: Step‑by‑step flow of a typical transaction."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773102438143}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1fc0833","parentId":"2143981b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:22.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the existing generate_reports.py script to see what's already implemented:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_VSkUPrnRjmxFjpjvja2aLXyQ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/scripts/generate_reports.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":585,"output":83,"cacheRead":17984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18652,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773102438149}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbff7c1c","parentId":"c1fc0833","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:22.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_VSkUPrnRjmxFjpjvja2aLXyQ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nGenerate all audit reports: EXECUTION_TRACE.md, FINDINGS.md, TEST_MATRIX.md, AUDIT_REPORT.md.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom utils_fs import read_file, write_file, read_json, write_json, ensure_dir\n\nWORKSPACE_ROOT = Path(os.getenv('WORKSPACE', '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace'))\n\ndef get_case_root(project_key, case_id):\n    return WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'projects' / project_key / 'code_audit' / case_id\n\ndef generate_execution_trace(project_key, case_id):\n    \"\"\"Generate EXECUTION_TRACE.md based on entrypoints and dependency graph.\"\"\"\n    case_root = get_case_root(project_key, case_id)\n    entrypoints_path = case_root / 'ENTRYPOINTS.json'\n    graph_path = case_root / 'DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json'\n    if not entrypoints_path.exists() or not graph_path.exists():\n        print(\"Missing entrypoints or graph. Run detect_entrypoints.py and build_dependency_graph.py first.\")\n        return\n\n    entrypoints = read_json(entrypoints_path)\n    graph = read_json(graph_path)\n\n    trace = \"# Execution Trace\\n\\n\"\n    trace += \"## Entry Points\\n\"\n    for ep in entrypoints.get('entrypoints', []):\n        if ep['type'] == 'vf_page':\n            trace += f\"- Visualforce page `{ep['file']}` using controller `{ep.get('controller', '?')}`\\n\"\n        elif ep['type'] == 'lwc':\n            trace += f\"- LWC component `{ep['component']}` referencing Apex classes: \"\n            for ref in ep.get('apex_references', []):\n                trace += f\"`{ref['class']}.{ref['method']}` \"\n            trace += \"\\n\"\n        elif ep['type'] == 'apex_aura':\n            trace += f\"- Apex class `{ep['class']}` with @AuraEnabled methods: {', '.join(ep.get('aura_enabled_methods', []))}\\n\"\n\n    trace += \"\\n## Typical Flow\\n\"\n    # Simplified: just list UI -> Controller -> Service -> Integration -> Trigger\n    trace += \"1. UI event (button click, page load)\\n\"\n    trace += \"2. Controller method invoked\\n\"\n    trace += \"3. Service/validation logic\\n\"\n    trace += \"4. DML operation\\n\"\n    trace += \"5. Trigger execution\\n\"\n    trace += \"6. Integration callouts (if any)\\n\"\n    trace += \"7. Response returned to UI\\n\"\n\n    # Add actual dependencies from graph\n    trace += \"\\n## Dependencies Identified\\n\"\n    for edge in graph.get('edges', []):\n        from_node = graph['nodes'][edge['from']]\n        to_node = graph['nodes'][edge['to']]\n        trace += f\"- `{from_node.get('name', '?')}` → `{to_node.get('name', '?')}` ({edge.get('type', '?')})\\n\"\n\n    write_file(case_root / 'EXECUTION_TRACE.md', trace)\n    print(f\"Written {case_root / 'EXECUTION_TRACE.md'}\")\n\ndef generate_findings(project_key, case_id):\n    \"\"\"Generate FINDINGS.md with common issues (placeholder).\"\"\"\n    case_root = get_case_root(project_key, case_id)\n    # In a real implementation, this would analyze code for patterns.\n    # For now, create a template.\n    findings = \"# Audit Findings\\n\\n\"\n    findings += \"## Security\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] FLS/CRUD checks missing\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] SOQL injection risk\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Secrets in code\\n\"\n    findings += \"\\n## Governor Limits\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] SOQL in loops\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] DML in loops\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Heap size risk\\n\"\n    findings += \"\\n## Performance\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Non‑selective queries\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Missing indexes\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] View state bloated\\n\"\n    findings += \"\\n## Maintainability\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Long methods\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Tight coupling\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Missing comments\\n\"\n    findings += \"\\n## Testing\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Low test coverage\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] Missing negative tests\\n\"\n    findings += \"- [ ] No mock for callouts\\n\"\n\n    write_file(case_root / 'FINDINGS.md', findings)\n    print(f\"Written {case_root / 'FINDINGS.md'}\")\n\ndef generate_test_matrix(project_key, case_id):\n    \"\"\"Generate TEST_MATRIX.md with test scenarios.\"\"\"\n    case_root = get_case_root(project_key, case_id)\n    entrypoints_path = case_root / 'ENTRYPOINTS.json'\n    if not entrypoints_path.exists():\n        print(\"Missing entrypoints. Run detect_entrypoints.py first.\")\n        return\n\n    entrypoints = read_json(entrypoints_path)\n    matrix = \"# Test Matrix\\n\\n\"\n    matrix += \"| Scenario | Trigger Action | Expected System Behavior | Related Code |\\n\"\n    matrix += \"|----------|----------------|--------------------------|--------------|\\n\"\n\n    for ep in entrypoints.get('entrypoints', []):\n        if ep['type'] == 'vf_page':\n            matrix += f\"| User loads page `{ep['file']}` | Page load | Controller constructor runs, page renders | `{ep.get('controller', '?')}` |\\n\"\n            matrix += f\"| User clicks save button | Command button action | Controller save method executes DML | `{ep.get('controller', '?')}.save` |\\n\"\n        elif ep['type'] == 'lwc':\n            for ref in ep.get('apex_references', []):\n                matrix += f\"| LWC `{ep['component']}` calls `{ref['method']}` | Button click | Apex method `{ref['class']}.{ref['method']}` runs, returns result | `{ref['class']}.{ref['method']}` |\\n\"\n        elif ep['type'] == 'apex_aura':\n            for method in ep.get('aura_enabled_methods', []):\n                matrix += f\"| Lightning component calls `{method}` | Client‑side action | Apex method `{ep['class']}.{method}` executes | `{ep['class']}.{method}` |\\n\"\n\n    write_file(case_root / 'TEST_MATRIX.md', matrix)\n    print(f\"Written {case_root / 'TEST_MATRIX.md'}\")\n\ndef generate_audit_report(project_key, case_id):\n    \"\"\"Generate comprehensive AUDIT_REPORT.md.\"\"\"\n    case_root = get_case_root(project_key, case_id)\n    manifest_path = case_root / 'MANIFEST.json'\n    if not manifest_path.exists():\n        print(\"MANIFEST.json not found.\")\n        return\n\n    manifest = read_json(manifest_path)\n    report = \"# Audit Report\\n\\n\"\n    report += f\"**Project**: {manifest['project_key']}\\n\"\n    report += f\"**Case ID**: {manifest['case_id']}\\n\"\n    report += f\"**Audit Date**: {datetime.utcnow().isoformat()}Z\\n\"\n    report += f\"**Total Files**: {manifest['total_files']}\\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Summary\\n\"\n    report += \"Brief overview of the audit scope and overall health.\\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Architecture Observations\\n\"\n    report += \"- UI Layer: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Controller Layer: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Service Layer: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Integration Layer: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Data Model: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Automation: \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Technical Risks\\n\"\n    report += \"- Governor Limits: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Performance: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Maintainability: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Testing: \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Security Risks\\n\"\n    report += \"- FLS/CRUD: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Injection: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Authentication: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Sharing: \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Performance Risks\\n\"\n    report += \"- Query selectivity: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Bulkification: \\n\"\n    report += \"- View state: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Async: \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Refactor Opportunities\\n\"\n    report += \"1. \\n\"\n    report += \"2. \\n\"\n    report += \"3. \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Design Alignment\\n\"\n    report += \"Compare with `salesforce‑architect` output if available.\\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Recommendations\\n\"\n    report += \"1. **Critical**: \\n\"\n    report += \"2. **High**: \\n\"\n    report += \"3. **Medium**: \\n\"\n    report += \"4. **Low**: \\n\\n\"\n\n    report += \"## Appendix\\n\"\n    report += \"- Files examined: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Snippets extracted: \\n\"\n    report += \"- Dependency graph: see DEPENDENCY_GRAPH.json\\n\"\n    report += \"- Execution trace: see EXECUTION_TRACE.md\\n\"\n\n    write_file(case_root / 'AUDIT_REPORT.md', report)\n    print(f\"Written {case_root / 'AUDIT_REPORT.md'}\")\n\ndef emit_incidents(project_key, case_id):\n    \"\"\"If critical issues found, emit incident via unified emitter.\"\"\"\n    # Path to the unified incident emitter script\n    script_path = WORKSPACE_ROOT / 'skills' / 'error-learning-loop' / 'scripts' / 'emit_incident.py'\n    if not script_path.exists():\n        print(f\"Error: emit_incident script not found at {script_path}\")\n        return False\n\n    # Parameters for the placeholder incident (same as before)\n    pattern_key = \"security|FLS_MISSING|apex\"\n    severity = \"S2\"\n    source_skill = \"salesforce-code-auditor\"\n    description = \"Missing FLS checks in Apex class\"\n    evidence = \"DemoController.cls line 5\"\n    incident_type = \"ERROR\"\n\n    # Build command\n    cmd = [\n        sys.executable, str(script_path),\n        pattern_key,\n        severity,\n        source_skill,\n        description,\n        evidence,\n        '--type', incident_type,\n        # trigger_learning is default True, no need to add --no-trigger\n    ]\n\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, check=True, capture_output=True, text=True)\n        print(result.stdout)\n        if result.stderr:\n            print(result.stderr)\n        print(f\"Incident emitted via unified emitter: {pattern_key}\")\n        return True\n    except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:\n        print(f\"Failed to emit incident: {e}\")\n        print(f\"stderr: {e.stderr}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='Generate audit reports.')\n    parser.add_argument('--project-key', required=True, help='Project identifier')\n    parser.add_argument('--case-id', required=True, help='Case identifier')\n    parser.add_argument('--emit-incidents', action='store_true', help='Emit incidents to learning system')\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    generate_execution_trace(args.project_key, args.case_id)\n    generate_findings(args.project_key, args.case_id)\n    generate_test_matrix(args.project_key, args.case_id)\n    generate_audit_report(args.project_key, args.case_id)\n    if args.emit_incidents:\n        emit_incidents(args.project_key, args.case_id)\n\n    print(\"\\nAll reports generated. Review and edit AUDIT_REPORT.md with actual findings.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773102442192}}
