{"type":"message","id":"6956174c","parentId":"b1183639","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:31.192Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_pZnbYCwjUvIGjoUHjkweWydJ","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773102451189}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0f43c7e","parentId":"6956174c","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:35.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me examine this file to understand the integration standards:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3FCZjBjs3jA5HOHanWsphTd3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-architect/references/CODE_AUDIT_HANDOFF_MODES.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":55,"output":85,"cacheRead":22272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22412,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773102451192}}
{"type":"message","id":"6624ad2e","parentId":"f0f43c7e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:35.459Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_3FCZjBjs3jA5HOHanWsphTd3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Code Audit Handoff Modes - Stable Reference Foundation\n\n**Purpose**: Define formal governance contract between Salesforce Architect and Code Auditor.\n**Status**: Reference asset - DO NOT regenerate on every run\n**Last Updated**: 2026-03-09\n\n## Handoff Governance Principles\n\n1. **Explicit contracts**: Clear request and response formats\n2. **Mode awareness**: Different modes for different scenarios\n3. **Severity handling**: Clear rules for handling findings\n4. **Architectural impact**: Findings must be assessed for architectural impact\n5. **Remediation tracking**: Clear process for addressing findings\n\n## Handoff Modes\n\n### Mode A — Architecture → Code Audit\n**Use when**: Architect needs current-state technical truth before design decisions.\n\n**Scenario Examples**:\n- Understanding existing codebase before redesign\n- Assessing technical debt impact on new design\n- Validating assumptions about current implementation\n- Identifying constraints for new features\n\n**Request Contract (Architect → Auditor)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Request - Mode A\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Architecture → Code Audit\n**Purpose**: <specific purpose for audit>\n\n### Audit Objectives\n1. <objective 1>\n2. <objective 2>\n3. <objective 3>\n\n### Scope Definition\n- **Included**: <files, components, areas>\n- **Excluded**: <files, components, areas>\n- **Depth**: <high-level review / detailed analysis>\n\n### Context Provided\n- Business process: <description>\n- Current pain points: <list>\n- Planned changes: <description>\n- Architectural concerns: <list>\n\n### Specific Questions\n1. <question 1>\n2. <question 2>\n3. <question 3>\n\n### Success Criteria\n- Technical constraints identified\n- Code quality assessment\n- Performance implications understood\n- Security risks identified\n```\n\n**Response Contract (Auditor → Architect)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode A\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Architecture → Code Audit\n\n### Executive Summary\n- Overall code health assessment\n- Key findings summary\n- Architectural implications\n\n### Technical Assessment\n- Code structure and organization\n- Design patterns used\n- Technical debt identified\n- Performance characteristics\n\n### Constraints & Limitations\n- Technical constraints for new development\n- Integration limitations\n- Scalability constraints\n- Security limitations\n\n### Risk Assessment\n- High-risk findings\n- Medium-risk findings\n- Low-risk findings\n- Risk mitigation suggestions\n\n### Recommendations for Architecture\n1. <recommendation 1>\n2. <recommendation 2>\n3. <recommendation 3>\n\n### Evidence\n- Code snippets supporting findings\n- Performance metrics\n- Security vulnerability details\n```\n\n### Mode B — Code Audit → Architecture\n**Use when**: Audit findings must change architecture decisions.\n\n**Scenario Examples**:\n- Critical security vulnerabilities found\n- Performance bottlenecks requiring architectural changes\n- Design patterns incompatible with findings\n- Technical debt requiring re-architecture\n\n**Request Contract (Architect → Auditor)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Request - Mode B\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Code Audit → Architecture\n**Purpose**: <specific purpose for audit>\n\n### Audit Trigger\n- <description of what triggered need for audit>\n\n### Focus Areas\n1. <area 1 - e.g., security vulnerabilities>\n2. <area 2 - e.g., performance bottlenecks>\n3. <area 3 - e.g., design pattern issues>\n\n### Architectural Context\n- Current architecture: <description>\n- Planned architecture: <description>\n- Known issues: <list>\n\n### Specific Concerns\n1. <concern 1>\n2. <concern 2>\n3. <concern 3>\n\n### Impact Assessment Requested\n- Architectural impact of findings\n- Remediation effort estimation\n- Risk of not addressing findings\n```\n\n**Response Contract (Auditor → Architect)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode B\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Code Audit → Architecture\n\n### Critical Findings Summary\n- Findings requiring architectural changes\n- Severity levels\n- Immediate risks\n\n### Architectural Impact Assessment\n- Current architecture compatibility\n- Required architectural changes\n- Impact on design decisions\n- Integration implications\n\n### Remediation Options\n1. **Option A**: <description, effort, impact>\n2. **Option B**: <description, effort, impact>\n3. **Option C**: <description, effort, impact>\n\n### Risk Analysis\n- Risk of current architecture\n- Risk of proposed changes\n- Risk of no changes\n- Risk mitigation strategies\n\n### Evidence-Based Recommendations\n- Recommended architectural changes\n- Justification based on findings\n- Implementation roadmap\n- Validation approach\n\n### Evidence\n- Code evidence for critical findings\n- Performance data\n- Security vulnerability details\n- Design pattern analysis\n```\n\n### Mode C — Design Validation Mode\n**Use when**: Architect needs to validate whether current implementation supports proposed design.\n\n**Scenario Examples**:\n- Validating design feasibility\n- Assessing implementation effort\n- Identifying gaps between design and implementation\n- Planning migration strategies\n\n**Request Contract (Architect → Auditor)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Request - Mode C\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Design Validation\n**Purpose**: Validate design feasibility\n\n### Design Context\n- Proposed design: <description or reference>\n- Design objectives: <list>\n- Success criteria: <list>\n\n### Validation Objectives\n1. Validate technical feasibility\n2. Assess implementation complexity\n3. Identify gaps between design and current implementation\n4. Estimate effort for implementation\n\n### Specific Validation Points\n1. <validation point 1>\n2. <validation point 2>\n3. <validation point 3>\n\n### Constraints to Consider\n- Technical constraints\n- Performance constraints\n- Security constraints\n- Integration constraints\n```\n\n**Response Contract (Auditor → Architect)**:\n```\n## Code Audit Report - Mode C\n\n**Project**: <project_key>\n**Audit Case ID**: <case_id>\n**Mode**: Design Validation\n\n### Design Feasibility Assessment\n- Overall feasibility: <feasible / partially feasible / not feasible>\n- Key feasibility concerns\n- Supporting evidence\n\n### Gap Analysis\n- Gaps between design and current implementation\n- Missing components\n- Incompatible patterns\n- Integration challenges\n\n### Implementation Complexity\n- Effort estimation\n- Complexity factors\n- Risk factors\n- Dependencies\n\n### Recommendations\n1. **Design adjustments**: <suggested changes>\n2. **Implementation approach**: <recommended approach>\n3. **Risk mitigation**: <suggested mitigations>\n4. **Validation strategy**: <suggested validation>\n\n### Evidence\n- Code analysis supporting findings\n- Complexity metrics\n- Gap analysis details\n- Feasibility assessment data\n```\n\n## Severity Handling Rules\n\n### Severity Levels\n**CRITICAL (Sev1)**:\n- Security vulnerabilities allowing unauthorized access\n- Data loss or corruption risks\n- Performance issues causing system failure\n- Architectural flaws requiring complete rework\n\n**Blocking Rule**: Must be addressed before architectural finalization\n\n**HIGH (Sev2)**:\n- Security vulnerabilities with significant impact\n- Performance issues affecting user experience\n- Code quality issues requiring significant rework\n- Design pattern violations with architectural impact\n\n**Blocking Rule**: Should be addressed before finalization, may have workarounds\n\n**MEDIUM (Sev3)**:\n- Code quality issues requiring moderate rework\n- Performance optimizations needed\n- Minor security concerns\n- Design improvements suggested\n\n**Blocking Rule**: Not blocking, but should be addressed in next release\n\n**LOW (Sev4)**:\n- Code style issues\n- Minor optimizations\n- Documentation improvements\n- Test coverage improvements\n\n**Blocking Rule**: Not blocking, address as capacity allows\n\n### Severity Escalation Rules\n1. **Multiple MEDIUM findings** → Consider escalating to HIGH if cumulative impact significant\n2. **HIGH findings in critical path** → Consider escalating to CRITICAL\n3. **Sev2 findings with workarounds** → May be downgraded to Sev3 if workaround approved\n4. **Sev3 findings with security impact** → Must be escalated to Sev2\n\n## When Findings Block Architectural Finalization\n\n### Absolute Blocking Conditions\n1. **CRITICAL security vulnerabilities** without approved mitigation\n2. **Architectural flaws** requiring design changes\n3. **Performance issues** making solution unusable\n4. **Integration failures** preventing core functionality\n\n### Conditional Blocking\n1. **HIGH severity findings** may block if:\n   - No workaround available\n   - Impact on core functionality\n   - Security/compliance implications\n2. **Multiple MEDIUM findings** may block if:\n   - Cumulative impact significant\n   - Affects maintainability\n   - Increases technical debt beyond threshold\n\n### Non-Blocking Conditions\n1. **LOW severity findings**\n2. **MEDIUM findings** with approved workarounds\n3. **Code style issues** without functional impact\n4. **Documentation gaps** without operational impact\n\n## Request/Response Quality Standards\n\n### Request Quality Requirements\n1. **Clear objectives**: Specific, measurable audit objectives\n2. **Defined scope**: Clear boundaries for audit\n3. **Adequate context**: Sufficient business/technical context\n4. **Specific questions**: Focused questions for auditor\n5. **Success criteria**: Clear definition of successful audit\n\n### Response Quality Requirements\n1. **Evidence-based**: All findings supported by code evidence\n2. **Actionable**: Clear recommendations for next steps\n3. **Structured**: Consistent format across audits\n4. **Prioritized**: Findings sorted by severity and impact\n5. **Architect-focused**: Information presented for architectural decisions\n\n### Validation Checklist\n**Before submitting request**:\n- [ ] Objectives clear and specific\n- [ ] Scope well-defined\n- [ ] Context adequate\n- [ ] Questions focused\n- [ ] Success criteria defined\n\n**Before accepting response**:\n- [ ] Evidence provided for all findings\n- [ ] Severity levels appropriate\n- [ ] Recommendations actionable\n- [ ] Architectural impact assessed\n- [ ] Format follows contract\n\n## Integration with Project State Machine\n\n### Audit Timing Rules\n1. **DISCOVERY phase**: Mode A audits to understand current state\n2. **DESIGN phase**: Mode C audits to validate design feasibility\n3. **ARCH_REVIEW phase**: Mode B audits for architectural validation\n4. **CODE_AUDIT phase**: Formal audit as part of state progression\n5. **REMEDIATION phase**: Follow-up audits to validate fixes\n\n### State Transition Impact\n1. **CODE_AUDIT → ARCH_REVIEW**: Findings may require architectural changes\n2. **ARCH_REVIEW → REMEDIATION**: Critical findings require remediation\n3. **REMEDIATION → FINALIZED**: All blocking findings must be resolved\n4. **Any state → CODE_AUDIT**: Can trigger audit at any phase if needed\n\n### Project README Integration\n**Required README sections**:\n```\n## Code Audits\n- Case ID: <case_id>\n- Mode: <A/B/C>\n- Date: <timestamp>\n- Findings: <summary>\n- Status: <open / in remediation / closed>\n\n## Audit History\n- <case_id_1>: <date> - <mode> - <status>\n- <case_id_2>: <date> - <mode> - <status>\n```\n\n## Incident Reporting for Handoff Failures\n\n### Request Failures\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|request_incomplete|missing_objectives`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|request_unclear|scope_ambiguous`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|context_insufficient|auditor_blocked`\n\n### Response Failures\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|response_incomplete|missing_evidence`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|response_unactionable|recommendations_vague`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|severity_misclassified|risk_underestimated`\n\n### Handoff Process Failures\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|handoff_missing|contract_not_followed`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|mode_mismatch|wrong_mode_selected`\n- `salesforce|CODE_AUDIT|integration_failed|project_state_inconsistent`\n\n## Continuous Improvement\n\n### Handoff Pattern Analysis\n1. **Success patterns**: What handoff approaches work best?\n2. **Failure patterns**: Common handoff failure modes\n3. **Efficiency metrics**: Time from request to actionable response\n4. **Quality metrics**: Response completeness and usefulness\n\n### Contract Evolution\n1. **Quarterly review**: Review and update handoff contracts\n2. **Incident-driven updates**: Update based on handoff failures\n3. **Technology updates**: Update for new audit techniques\n4. **Role feedback**: Incorporate architect and auditor feedback"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773102455452}}
